3) Example usage (any @Service or @Controller)

import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

import java.util.Map;

@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class SomeBusinessService {

    private final your.pkg.http.HttpPostClient http;

    public void callExternalApi() {
        String url = "https://api.example.com/v1/process";
        String json = """
            {
              "foo": "bar",
              "count": 1
            }
            """;

        // Optional headers (add correlation-id, auth, etc.)
        Map<String, String> hdrs = Map.of(
            "X-Correlation-Id", java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString()
        );

        // This will block until response arrives.
        // If HTTP 2xx -> returns body; else -> throws RuntimeException.
        String responseBody = http.postJson(url, json, hdrs);

        // Continue on success...
        System.out.println("OK: " + responseBody);
    }
}

Notes
	•	Thread-safe: RestTemplate is stateless and reused; method has no shared mutable state.
	•	Error handling: 4xx/5xx/timeouts produce clear exceptions with log entries.
	•	If you later need retries/circuit breakers, wrap http.postJson(...) with Resilience4j.